======================
Concatenation in java
======================

- Case 1
  - String in java can be combined using "+" operator

- Case 2
  - In case of integer variables "+" operator 
    performs arithmetic sum operation
  
- Case 3 
  - If integer variable is added with a string var
    then the output is a string variable
  
- Case 4 
  - If 2 integer variable are added the then added with a string
    then first teh arithmetic sum will be performed
    and then string concatination is done

- Case 5
  - If 2 integer varables are added after a string
    then whole statement is treated as string concatination 
    and arithmetic sum is not performed
    
- Ex
  String str1 = "Hello";
  String str2 = "World";
  
  int num1 = 1000;
  int num2 = 999;
  
  System.out.println(str1 + str2);  // HelloWorld
  System.out.println(num1 + num2);  // 1999
  
  System.out.println(num1 + num2 + str1 + str2);  // 1999HelloWorld
  System.out.println(str1 + str2 + num1 + num2);  // HelloWorld1000999

